Provenance: this work is a modern rewrite of The Unarchiver. Its legacy-format
support is provided by the newtua-formats crate family, whose decoders are
ported from XADMaster (© Dag Ågren and contributors, GNU LGPL). Because the
engine links those LGPL components, newtua-core is itself distributed under the
LGPL.

The engine also depends on four forced forks of third-party crates —
newtua-unrar, newtua-apfs, newtua-hfsplus and newtua-cdfs — which retain the
licenses of their respective upstream projects. Each fork's README explains why it exists
and states the license it carries.

RAR support and the UnRAR license. RAR archives are read through libunrar, by
way of the newtua-unrar fork. The UnRAR sources are not part of this
repository: Cargo fetches them (as unrar_sys) at build time. They carry a
license of their own (© Alexander Roshal) that permits use in any software
handling RAR archives, but forbids using the code to build a RAR-compatible
archiver.

That restriction reaches no user of this software. newtua never creates
archives — it extracts and lists only — so no RAR compressor can be derived
from it. Where a build does combine the two, the result is conveyed under
section 4 of the LGPL v3, which permits a Combined Work under other terms
provided the library is identified and its license supplied. Binary artifacts
published by this project ship the UnRAR license text alongside this notice.

